The paper presents an artificial intelligence research environment for training and evaluating intelligent agents in a massively multiplayer online role-playing game (MMORPG) setting. This involves the study of large-scale multiagent interaction, which is a common topic in the fields of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.AI. The paper also discusses the development of robust combat and navigation policies, which falls under the category of reinforcement learning, making cs.LG another likely sub-category. The paper also explores the concept of competition and niche-filling, which are topics in game theory (cs.GT) and multiagent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks in the training of agents, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.SI).
